Let $T$ be the $N \times N$ matrix with entries (indices modulo $N$):

$$T_{jj} = a, \qquad T_{j,j+1} = b, \qquad T_{j+1,j} = c \quad (j = 1,\dots,N),$$

where the index $N+1$ is identified with $1$ (periodic boundary conditions). All other entries are zero. The parameters $a,b,c \in \mathbb{C}$ are fixed.

```figure caption="Structure of the $N \times N$ periodic tridiagonal matrix $T$ with corner entries at $(1,N)$ and $(N,1)$."
